Popular singer, Justin Bieber has postponed his show after testing positive for the deadly COVID-19. Bieber, in a statement on his Twitter page, said he cancelled the show which was to hold at the T-Mobile Arena in Las Vegas on Sunday, February 20, after receiving the report of the COVID-19 test carried out a day before. He said he is disappointed about the postponement but his health is the number one priority. The tweet reads, “Due to positive COVID results within the Justice Tour family, we will, unfortunately, have to postpone Sunday’s show in Glendale “Justin is, of course, hugely disappointed, but the health and safety of his crew and fans is always his number one priority.”